<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-01-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-12-30T14:00:00-05:00" n="465" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d465">
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">No. 465</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                            </head>
                            <p>On January 14, 1952, President <persName corresp="#p_THS1">Truman</persName> announced that General
                                    <persName>Clark</persName>’s nomination as Ambassador to the
                                State of Vatican City was being withdrawn at
                                    <persName>Clark</persName>’s request. Documentation pertaining
                                to this announcement, as well as to the subsequent consideration
                                within the United States Government of the possible establishment of
                                diplomatic relations with the Vatican, is scheduled for publication
                                in <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1952-1954, volume
                                VI.</p>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>